task.summary: added example code of using Railway for Option from discussion in ReScript forum
added example code of using Railway for Option from discussion in ReScript forum
implemented Array.valuesIter to return Iterator of values of an array
Implement fixed key type for Map. key types supported are Array, Tuple2, and Tuple3.
Implement using values that are non-primitive for Set. value types supported are Array, Tuple2, and Tuple3.
implemented MakeWithPrimitives in Map_Ext and Set_Ext
Reimplemented AdjacencyList with Map_Ext and Set_Ext
Reimplemented bfs and dfs with AdjacencyList
Added Functor for Graph_Ext so that it supports non-primitive types
default Int, Float, BigInt for Serializable
Dijkstra now works with Tuple2 or any AdjacencyList that has non-primitive Node
unit tests for AdjacencyList and Dijkstra
Graph_Ext bfs and dfs now work with non-primitive types
use Option instead of raising exception in Priority Queue
mute warning of using raise() in rescript-v12.0.0-alpha.10. should remove once all raise() calls migrated to throw()
Added more tests for AStar. Added Array2D -> AdjacencyList function
AStar doesn't need to depend on AdjacencyList.
fixed BigInt logical ops (introduced in rescript-v12.0.0-alpha.11)
Graph_Ext no longer depends on AdjacencyList
